The paper deals with a fundamental problem in computer science related to understanding local properties of multi-dimensional data. The problem is related to testing pattern freeness in large d-dimensional arrays, which is a topic in data structures (cs.DS) and computational complexity (cs.CC). The paper also establishes several combinatorial results, which are relevant to computational geometry (cs.CG) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). Finally, the paper uses concepts from information theory (cs.IT) to analyze the testers.
